Package: snakeplot
Title: Serpentine (Snake) Plots for Survey and Activity Data
Version: 0.2.2
Authors@R: person("Mohammed", "Saqr", email = "saqr@saqr.me",
                  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Visualize timelines, longer sequences and temporally chained survey responses and experience sampling data using
    serpentine (snake). Supports distribution bars,
    tick-mark plots, inter-item correlation arcs, faceted multi-construct
    panels, and daily time-of-day positioning for ecological momentary
    assessment data. Uses only base 'R' graphics with zero external dependencies.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: graphics, grDevices, stats
LazyData: true
URL: https://github.com/mohsaqr/snakeplot
BugReports: https://github.com/mohsaqr/snakeplot/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
